About Swiss Re



   Swiss Re is one of the world’s leading providers of reinsurance, insurance and other forms of insurance-based risk transfer, working to make the world more resilient. We anticipate and manage a wide variety of risks, from natural catastrophes and climate change to cybercrime.

 At Swiss Re we combine experience with creative thinking and cutting-edge expertise to create new opportunities and solutions for our clients. This is possible thanks to the collaboration of more than 13,000 employees across the world.

 We offer a flexible working environment where curious and adaptable people thrive. Are you interested in joining us?




About the Role



  We are looking for a forward-thinking individual with a passion for data, analytics and technology to join the Property & Casualty (P&C) Analytics team.



  Swiss Re's data and analytics assets support our clients' P&C portfolios along the insurance value chain, from risk assessment to pricing to portfolio steering and accumulation control. As we continue to grow, we seek to extend our coverage to other geographies in Asia Pacific and lead the industry practice in how we apply statistical and ML methods to insurance problems.



  Your main responsibilities will include, however, are not limited to:



Support the planning and development of risk assets and data models for P&C Analytics;
Co-develop new solutions to bridge the gaps in our offering today, taking an end-to-end ownership from understanding the business need, acquiring data, modelling and communication of analysis;
Identify, evaluate and ingest data sources to enrich risk assessment and pricing for insurance;
Work hands-on in collaboration with a cross-functional team, from design to prototype, to productive implementation; and
Develop/expand your knowledge on P&C Insurance solutions;



  You will report into the P&C Analytics team but be an important part of a wider Solutions community within APAC, EMEA and globally.



About the Team



  P&C Solutions is one of the three pillars within the Swiss Re Reinsurance Business Unit. The pillar aims to contribute to clients’ business by providing solutions and services across the value chain. Our clients' needs are at the heart of what we do, as we make sure that our solutions and services help our clients grow and make commercial sense. It is within the directive of the team to be at the forefront of analytics understanding by driving the development of novel solutions through the combination of risk knowledge and data science capabilities.



About You



3+ years' experience in executing projects with technical background & analytical components, preferably within the re/insurance industry;
Good knowledge of the insurance market in ANZ, Japan or South-East Asia;
Advanced degree and education with quantitative background;
Strong analytical problem-solving skills, business focus, eagerness to learn new concepts and ability to assimilate complex, imperfect information;
Ability to find and interpret relevant datasets and judge their potential business impact;
Experience in R or Python;
Ability to develop strong working relations with business colleagues, building your network; and
Open and curious, quick-minded, fast-learner, creative.



  Experience in technical development and applying actuarial, machine learning or statistical analysis, including Geospatial analytics experience would be an advantage!



  Do you enjoy building a network with specialists from a multitude of fields and bringing together their input to get a wholistic picture? If so, we would love to hear from you!



  We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status


